    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-05-15T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-05-15T09:00:00-05:00" n="745"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d745">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/10965: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Leahy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vichy</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-05-15T16:00:00+02:00"
                            >May 15, 1941—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 15—1:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>558. A formal urgent communication embodying the instructions contained in the
                    Department’s telegram 409, May 14, 6 p.m., was handed personally to Rochat<note
                        n="69" xml:id="d745fn69">Charles Antoine Rochat, Acting Secretary General of
                        the French Ministry for Foreign Affairs.</note> at 4 p.m. this
                    afternoon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Leahy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
